<h1 class="title">Creating This Website</h1>
</header><p>
As it has taken me some time to research how to build this website to
my liking, I would like to share this knowledge with anyone who cares.
</p>

<p>
First of all, the technologies:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="https://orgmode.org/">Emacs Org mode</a>: the <a href="https://orgmode.org/manual/Publishing.html">Org Publish</a> package</li>
<li>Hosting using <a href="https://pages.github.com/">Github Pages</a></li>
</ul>
<p>
This is as basic as it can get. The idea is as follows: first, you
write an Org Publish configuration file. Then, you write your webpages
in Org files. Next, the html files are generated through the Org
Publish package. Lastly, the generated html files are put in the git
repository that represents your Github Pages location.
</p>

<p>
The greatest help of all came from these two articles:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="https://www.taingram.org/blog/org-mode-blog.html">Building a Emacs Org-Mode Blog</a></li>
<li><a href="https://orgmode.org/worg/org-tutorials/org-publish-html-tutorial.html">Publishing Org-mode files to HTML</a></li>
</ul>

<p>
Lastly, I really liked these resources:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="https://practicaltypography.com/">Practical Typography</a> &#x2014; Highly recommended</li>
<li><a href="http://colormind.io/">Colormind</a></li>
<li><a href="https://jgthms.com/web-design-in-4-minutes/">Webdesign in 4 minutes</a></li>
</ul>

<p>
Good luck.
</p>
</div>
